<HL>
   General Dynamics Launch Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
09/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   GD GE
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<LP>
   SAN DIEGO -- General Dynamics Commercial Launch Services
Inc., a unit of St Louis-based General Dynamics Corp. said it
signed a contract with a unit of General Electric Co. to
launch a Japanese communications satellite.
   Terms weren't disclosed, but General Dynamics usually
charges between $50 million and $60 million for its Atlas I
launch service. The satellite will be built by GE's
Astro-Space division in East Windsor, N.J., and launched in
April from Cape Canaveral, Fla.
</LP>
