<IN>
SPECIALTY RETAILERS (OTS)
</IN>
<LP>
   SAGINAW, Mich. -- Wolohan Lumber Co., a lumber and
building materials retailer, said its September sales rose
10% to $30 million from $27.2 million a year earlier. Sales
at stores open at least one year decreased 3%.
   Sales for the first eight months of this year rose 11% to
$201 million from $181.9 million a year earlier.
Comparable-store sales increased 4.5%.
