<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)
BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)
</IN>
<LP>
   TAMPA, Fla. -- Bicoastal Corp., formerly Singer Co., said
it completed the sale of its Link-Miles Ltd. subsidiary to
Thomson (U.K.) Holding Ltd., a subsidiary of the French
state-controlled defense and electronics group Thomson-CSF
S.A.
   The transaction was announced in May.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Under terms, Thomson (U.K.) Holding paid some $70 million
of the $100 million purchase price at closing, with $20
million deposited in escrow and $10 million retained by
Thomson for contingencies.
   Based in Lancing, England, Link-Miles develops and
produces simulators for world-wide military and commercial
applications.
   Bicoastal is operating with protection against creditor
lawsuits under Chapter 11 of federal bankruptcy law.
