   Business Brief -- United Telecommunications Inc.:
   US Sprint Subsidiary Gets
   $127 Million in Contracts
</HL>
<DATE>
09/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   UT ITT X.FRE
</CO>
<IN>
TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)
</IN>
<LP>
   US Sprint Communications Co., a unit of United
Telecommunications Inc., said it reached contracts with
several companies for telecommunications services with a
total value of $127 million.
   National Carriers' Buyers Network, a San Jose,
Calif.-based group of small-to-medium size regional carriers,
agreed to a two-year, $78 million contract for a package of
telecommunications services that supplement its personal
networks and provide expanded service to its customers. The
regional carriers buy telecommunications services and then
repackage them for smaller customers.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   San Diego-based American Healthcare Systems signed an
agreement with Sprint estimated at more than $36 million over
three years. Sprint said it will design and implement a
communications network that links American Healthcare's 1,100
facilities. Sprint will also provide public pay telephone,
patient calling and employee benefit-related services for the
health-care alliance.
   ITT Corp. signed a three-year agreement with Sprint valued
at $10.8 million to provide a variety of telecommunications
services. Based in New York, ITT is a diversified
multinational corporation.
   Fireman's Fund Mortgage Corp. awarded U.S. Sprint a
two-year, $2.2 million contract for a multiple-location WATS
system on a national basis. Based in Farmington Hills, Mich.,
Fireman's Fund Mortgage is a subsidiary of Fireman's Fund
Insurance Co. of Novato, Calif.
</TEXT>
