<HL>
   Business Brief -- Ogden Corp.:
   Allied Division to Acquire
   ARA's Ground Services Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
09/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   OG X.ARA
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
INDUSTRIAL &amp; COMMERCIAL SERVICES, LEASING, CLEANING (ICS)
</IN>
<LP>
   An Ogden Corp. unit agreed to acquire the Ground Services
Inc. subsidiary of ARA Group Inc.
   Terms weren't disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Ogden's Allied Aviation Services division, which has been
expanding, provides more than $400 million annually of
services -- baggage, ticketing, food service, fueling and
others -- to a number of airports and airlines. Ground
Services, with annual revenue of $35 million, cleans
aircraft, warehouses cargo and handles baggage.
   Closely held ARA, based in Philadelphia, has businesses in
food service, uniform rental, magazine and book distribution,
child care and nursing homes. The company also manages
hospital emergency rooms.
   New York-based Ogden provides services to entertainment,
aviation, government and building markets. Ogden also
provides hazardous-waste and municipal solid-waste
incineration services.
</TEXT>
